Troubleshooting Tips
Issue: PowerShell script fails with permission error

Solution: Ensure script has execute permissions (chmod +x script.ps1)
Check file paths are correct relative to script location
Issue: Log monitoring shows no authentication events

Solution: Authentication logs may require sudo access
Use sudo grep for /var/log/auth.log access
Verify log files exist on your system
Issue: Change detector creates false positives

Solution: Delete baseline files and recreate after system is stable
Some files change frequently (e.g., logs) - exclude from monitoring
Use file content hash instead of modification time for better accuracy
Issue: HTML report not displaying correctly

Solution: Verify all HTML tags are properly closed
Check JSON files exist before parsing
Use jq to validate JSON syntax
Issue: Scheduled tasks not executing

Solution: Verify cron service is running (systemctl status cron)
Check script paths are absolute in crontab
Review cron logs: grep CRON /var/log/syslog
